Here's a clean implementation using the CommunityToolkit.Mvvm source generators, which is the recommended approach for .NET MAUI:

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace YourApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isLoading;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        IsLoading = true;
        try
        {
            // Replace with your actual service call
            await Task.Delay(500);
            Name = "Widget Pro";
            Price = 29.99m;
            IsAvailable = true;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsLoading = false;
        }
    }
}
```

**How it works:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` generates public properties (`Name`, `Price`, etc.) with `INotifyPropertyChanged` calls — no boilerplate needed.
- `[RelayCommand]` generates a `LoadCommand` (IAsyncRelayCommand) from `LoadAsync`, which also disables the command while running.
- The class must be `partial` so the source generator can emit the backing code.

**XAML binding example:**

```xml
<Label Text="{Binding Name}" />
<Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}" />
<Switch IsToggled="{Binding IsAvailable}" />
<Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
<ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsLoading}" />
```

**Required NuGet package:**

```
dotnet add package CommunityToolkit.Mvvm
```
